                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="178.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Atoms are the fundamental building blocks of matter. Each atom consists of a nucleus made up of protons and neutrons, surrounded by a cloud of electrons. Early models such as Dalton's solid sphere model have evolved into more advanced ones, including the quantum mechanical model, which describes the behavior of electrons in terms of probabilities rather than fixed orbits." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
