                  <Label layoutX="30.0" layoutY="363.0" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="686.0" text="The Periodic Table">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI Semibold" size="25.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="435.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The periodic table organizes elements based on increasing atomic number and recurring chemical properties. Elements in the same group share similar characteristics due to having the same number of valence electrons. Trends across periods and down groups, such as atomic radius, electronegativity, and ionization energy, help predict element behavior." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="539.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Understanding the layout of the periodic table enables students to identify metals, nonmetals, and metalloids and to anticipate how elements might react with one another. This predictive power is fundamental in chemical analysis and synthesis." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
