                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="680.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Chemical bonding involves the attraction between atoms to form molecules and compounds. The main types are ionic bonds (transfer of electrons), covalent bonds (sharing of electrons), and metallic bonds (delocalized electrons in a metal lattice). Each type results in substances with different properties." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="762.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Bonding theories such as Lewis structures and VSEPR (Valence Shell Electron Pair Repulsion) theory help visualize molecule shapes and predict their behavior. Understanding bonding is key to grasping how substances interact and change during chemical reactions." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
